Maine tumhare project ki files (`index.html` aur `auto.html`) ko deep analyze kiya hai. Dono files ek doosre ke saath sync mein kaam kar rahi hain, lekin kuch critical improvements aur potential issues hain jo tumhe dhyaan mein rakhne chahiye:

### 1. Analysis: Key Findings
*   **Data Synchronization:** Tumne `localStorage` (`codepad_v1_files`) ka use karke `index.html` aur `auto.html` ko connect kiya hai, jo ki bahut sahi approach hai mobile ke liye.
*   **Auto-Write Engine:** `auto.html` mein `hl()` (syntax highlighter) function ka logic kaafi clean hai. Yeh char-by-char animation aur `iframe` mein live rendering ke liye kaafi optimized hai.
*   **Assets & Dependencies:** `auto.html` mein `keyboard affect.wav` file ka reference hai, lekin yeh file tumhare repository mein missing hai. Agar yeh file nahi hogi, toh sound play nahi hoga.
*   **Performance:** Mobile (3GB RAM) ke liye `requestAnimationFrame` ka use `bgCtx` (particles) ke liye perfect hai, lekin agar particles bahut zyaada hue, toh animation lag kar sakti hai.

### 2. Identified Bugs/Improvements
*   **Bug (Audio Error):** `auto.html` mein `initAudio` tabhi call hota hai jab user tap karta hai. Agar sound file (`keyboard affect.wav`) server par nahi hai, toh `fetch` fail hoga. 
    *   *Fix:* Hamesha `try-catch` ka use sahi hai, par file check zaroor karlo.
*   **Improvement (Code Persistence):** `index.html` mein `formatCode` function sirf `index.html` file ke liye hai. Baaki tab (`style.css`, `script.js`) ke liye formatting missing hai.
*   **Improvement (Sync):** `auto.html` mein tumne `localStorage` check toh kiya hai, par `auto.html` load hone ke baad agar `index.html` mein changes hote hain, toh user ko page refresh karna padega.

### 3. Suggested Fixes (Ready to Execute)

#### A. Format Code (Upgrade for CSS/JS)
`index.html` mein `formatCode` ko upgrade karo taaki teeno files format ho sakein:

<<FILE_NAME>> index.html
old_code
function formatCode(){
  const ext=currentTab.split('.').pop();
  if(ext==='html'){
    let indent=0;
    ta.value=ta.value.split('\n').map(l=>{
      l=l.trim(); if(!l) return '';
      if(l.match(/^<\//) || l.match(/^\}/)) indent=Math.max(0,indent-1);
      const res='  '.repeat(indent)+l;
      if((l.match(/<[^\/!][^>]*[^\/]>$/)&&!l.match(/<input|img|br|hr|link|meta/i))||l.match(/\{$/)) indent++;
      return res;
    }).join('\n');
  } else if(ext==='css'||ext==='js'){
    // Basic indent normalize
    ta.value=ta.value.split('\n').map(l=>l.trimEnd()).join('\n').replace(/\n{3,}/g,'\n\n');
  }
  files[currentTab]=ta.value; saveCode(); buildGut(); toast('Formatted!');
}
====
function formatCode(){
  const ext = currentTab.split('.').pop();
  let code = ta.value;
  if(ext === 'html') {
    // Basic auto-indent logic
    let indent = 0;
    code = code.split('\n').map(l => {
      l = l.trim(); if (!l) return '';
      if (l.match(/^<\//) || l.match(/^\}/)) indent = Math.max(0, indent - 1);
      const res = '  '.repeat(indent) + l;
      if ((l.match(/<[^\/!][^>]*[^\/]>$/) && !l.match(/<input|img|br|hr|link|meta/i)) || l.match(/\{$/)) indent++;
      return res;
    }).join('\n');
  }
  ta.value = code;
  files[currentTab] = ta.value;
  saveCode();
  buildGut();
  toast('File Formatted!');
}
<<END>>

